    "body": "### Problem\n\nneovim started in mosh leaves stray symbols on the screen and/or corrupts whole terminal\r\n\r\nCould be related to https://github.com/mobile-shell/mosh/issues/1041\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nwget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LazyVim/LazyVim/main/lua/lazyvim/config/init.lua\r\nnvim --clean init.lua\r\n\r\nGo top-bottom several times (gg, G, gg, G, gg, G)\r\n\r\nYou'll have stray symbols left after a while:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/82057/0548fc50-16c8-41a6-9ce8-a9706ebd3cc4)\r\n\r\nIf you try it with LazyVim default config it's even worse, it looks like the issue is triggered with unicode symbols:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"714\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/82057/8342724f-181e-40e8-8163-d9629d865efd\">\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo stray characters left behind.\r\n\r\nLazyVim should look like that:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"669\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/82057/9a79300c-dd82-4ba9-8739-da21a59d8f04\">\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.5, also tried v0.10.0-dev-2110+g2fce95ec43\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 8.2 or 9.1 works fine\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux (archlinux, centOS), macOS 14.2.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nmosh-1.4.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nmosh-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
